Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:12.000
 If you want even more fun with Windows 8, - 

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:15.200
 - then you have to go into the engine room and adjust as you wish. 

00:00:15.800 --> 00:00:20.100
 It takes place in the 'Control Panel', where update, sound and appearance are controlled. 

00:00:20.650 --> 00:00:25.150
 Right-click the Windows icon and select from the 'Control Panel' menu. 

00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:29.900
 Updates for Windows take place under the item 'Windows update' - 

00:00:29.900 --> 00:00:36.900
 - and by clicking 'Search for updates', a search is initiated. In this case, Windows is updated. 

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:42.800
 Under 'Change settings', the automation of these updates can be set. 

00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:48.900
 You can choose to have all updates installed. In the next selection, the update is downloaded, - 

00:00:48.900 --> 00:00:54.900
 - but you have to start the update yourself. In the third choice, it looks for the update - 

00:00:54.900 --> 00:00:59.500
 - and you have to choose the updates for download and then installation. 

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:06.000
 The last option is to search, download and install any updates yourself. 

00:01:06.300 --> 00:01:11.200
 In the 'Hardware &amp; Sound' item, the sound is controlled from the 'Sound' sub-item. 

00:01:11.500 --> 00:01:17.000
 Select audio output from the 'Playback' tab - speakers or headphones. 

00:01:18.100 --> 00:01:21.500
 Under the 'Recording' tab, the microphone can be set. 

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:27.600
 The small sounds that Windows plays in given situations, such as. receiving an email, - 

00:01:27.600 --> 00:01:32.000
 - called system sounds and set under the tab 'Sounds'. 

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:36.100
 The last tab is 'Communication', where all sounds can be quickly reduced - 

00:01:36.100 --> 00:01:41.400
 - in power or interrupted completely when the computer is used - 

00:01:41.400 --> 00:01:44.000
 - to make or receive phone calls. 

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:47.900
 The background image can be changed according to taste and personal style. 

00:01:47.900 --> 00:01:52.100
 Right-click on the desktop and select from the 'Personal settings' menu. 

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:55.400
 There are standards in place that can be selected, but there are - 

00:01:55.400 --> 00:02:00.000
 - more to download for free from 'Get More Themes Online'. 

00:02:01.800 --> 00:02:07.100
 Click on the download and now the selected car theme appears under the heading 'My themes 2'. 

00:02:07.100 --> 00:02:11.800
 Under 'Choose desktop background' you can choose yourself - 

00:02:11.800 --> 00:02:15.100
 - the pictures shown in the theme, and in the box 'Image placement' - 

00:02:15.100 --> 00:02:20.000
 - a desired adaptation of how much the image is to fill the screen can be adjusted. 

00:02:21.900 --> 00:02:27.400
 Last but not least, the picture shift can be adjusted, that is, the frequency of switching between the images. 

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:31.900
 Under 'Color and appearance' the color of the beams is regulated either by - 

00:02:31.900 --> 00:02:36.000
 - use of direct color selection or shading regulated as shown. 

00:02:36.050 --> 00:02:43.900
 'Increased accessibility' opens up for everyone to use Windows regardless of physical disabilities. 

00:02:43.980 --> 00:02:48.080
 When starting 'Magnifying glass', the user interface can be enlarged many times. 

00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:55.700
 If someone has a touch screen for a keyboard, that option can be activated. 

00:02:57.300 --> 00:03:00.000
 And it is possible to read from the written screen. 

